## ğŸ§  Code Structure Overview

### ğŸ§± Core Components

- `struct User` / `struct Product` / `struct Order` â€“ Data models  
- `registerUser()` â€“ Handles new user signups  
- `loginUser()` / `loginAdmin()` â€“ Authenticates users/admins  
- `addProduct()`, `viewProducts()` â€“ Product CRUD operations  
- `addToCart()`, `removeFromCart()`, `checkout()` â€“ Cart functions  
- `saveData()`, `loadData()` â€“ File operations  
- `viewOrders()`, `markOrderShipped()` â€“ Admin order management  
- `changePassword()`, `withdrawFunds()` â€“ Admin utilities

---

## ğŸ§® Data Types Used

- ğŸ§± Structs: For user, product, and order records  
- ğŸ—ƒï¸ Linked Lists: Used instead of arrays for product storage
- ğŸ§± Priority Queues: For Premium Users.
- ğŸ”¤ Strings: Usernames, passwords, emails, product names  
- ğŸ“‚ File Streams: For reading/writing data persistently  
- ğŸ·ï¸ Enums / Flags: Used for user roles and order status

---

## âš–ï¸ Design Decisions

| Feature                  |   Pros                                               |    Cons                                      |
|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| File-based persistence   | Simple, fast, and easy to debug                      | Not suitable for scaling to large data       |
| Role-based system        | Clear separation of privileges                       | Requires more validation logic               |
| Console-based UI         | Lightweight and accessible                           | Limited UX / no GUI                          |
| Validation functions     | Prevent bad data and increase security               | Slightly more complex input logic            |
| Linked list for products | Efficient dynamic memory usage                       | More overhead than vectors                   |

---


